answers.answer: It could be a number of things. Don't stress yourself I'm sure you'll be fine.
My last midwife app i also had protein in my urine as well as swelling in feet/fingers wen they checked my blood pressure it was perfect so they said not to worry bout the protein :-) im 23+2weeks..

Every dr appointment I have I've had a trace of protein they just tell me to drink more water. If the strip said a really high amount I'm sure you would have known and they would have done something if they were concerned
no I have never had a UTI

Protein sometimes passes through. I have had that happen twice along with blood in my urine. My doctor checked me and everything was okay. I don't have preeclampsia and I am 32 weeks tomorrow. If they haven't called you, I would say everything is okay. My doctor said they only call if something is wrong. So in this case no news is good news. :)
